        synonyms: "vadanti – they say; tat – that; tattva-vidaḥ – those who know the truth; tattvam – the Absolute Truth; yat – which; jñānam – knowledge; advayam – non-dual; brahma iti – known as brahma; paramātmā iti – known as Paramātmā; bhagavān iti – known as Bhagavān; śabdyate – it is so declared.",
        translation: "Great seers of the truth, who understand the nature of the Absolute Truth, describe that Supreme non-dual truth in three as impersonal brahma, localized Paramātmā and Svayam Bhagavān, the Personality of Godhead."
