        ref: "Śrī Caitanya-caritāmṛta, Madhya-līlā (22.107)",
        synonyms: "nitya-siddha – eternally established [as a potentiality in the heart of conditioned souls, and as a fully-fledged reality in the heart of the nitya-siddha guru]; kṛṣṇa-prema – love of Kṛṣṇa; sādhya – to be attained through the practice of sādhana; kabhu – at any time; naya – not; śravaṇa-ādi – by hearing, etc.; śuddha – purified; citte – in the heart; karaye udaya – it is aroused.",
