        synonyms: "teṣām – for them; eva – only; anukampa-artham – out of compassion; aham – I; ajñāna-jam – born of ignorance; tamaḥ – darkness [in the form of material existence]; nāśayāmi – I destroy; ātma-bhāva-sthaḥ – situated within the intelligence [of the jīvātmā]; jñāna-dīpena – with the lamp of transcendental knowledge; bhāsvatā – with the blazing.",
        translation: "Only out of compassion for devotees who are exclusively devoted to Me do I, dwelling within their intelligence, destroy with the blazing lamp of transcendental knowledge the darkness of material existence, which is born of ignorance."
