        translation: "A bhakta who has taken birth in a family of dog-eaters, but who has dedicated his mind, words, activities and wealth to the lotus feet of Śrī Kṛṣṇa, is superior to a brāhmaṇa endowed with all the twelve brahminical qualities, but who has no bhakti for Śrī Kṛṣṇa. Such a bhakta, although of lowly birth, can purify himself and his whole family, whereas the brāhmaṇa, who is filled with pride due to his superior social position, cannot even purify himself."
