        sanskrit: "antaḥ kṛṣṇaṁ bahir gauraṁ darśitāṅgādi-vaibhavam\nkalau saṅkīrtanādyaiḥ sma kṛṣṇa-caitanyam āśritāḥ",
        ref: "Tattva-sandarbha (2), Śrīla Jīva Gosvāmī",
        synonyms: "antaḥ – internally; kṛṣṇam – Śrī Kṛṣṇa; bahiḥ – externally; gauram – fair-coloured; darśita – displayed; aṅga – limbs; ādi – beginning with; vaibhavam – expansions; kalau – in the Age of Kali; saṅkīrtana-ādyaiḥ – by congregational chanting, etc.; sma – certainly; kṛṣṇa-caitanyam – unto Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; āśritāḥ – sheltered.",
