        synonyms: "tasmin – there; mahat – of great saintly persons; mukharitāḥ – emanating from the mouths; madhu-bhit – of the killer of the Madhu demon; caritra – the activities or the character; pīyūṣa – of nectar; śeṣa – surplus; saritaḥ – rivers; paritaḥ – all around; sravanti – flow; tāḥ – all of them; ye – they who; pibanti – drink; avitṛṣaḥ – without being satisfied; nṛpa – O King; gāḍha – attentive; karṇaiḥ – with their ears; tān – them; na – never; spṛśanti – touch; aśana – hunger; tṛṭ – thirst; bhaya – fear; śoka – lamentation; mohāḥ – illusion.",
